{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"43722cbb-4638-4556-af3c-c0857e7672f0","content":"The directory is empty — there's no existing file to edit. Here's exactly how to do the conversion:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to enable compiled bindings\n\nIn your `<ContentPage>` root element, add the XML namespace for your viewmodel and the `x:DataType` attribute:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage\n    xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n    xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n    xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n    x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n    x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n    Title=\"Settings\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"Theme\" />\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Notifications\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"Font Size\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Current: {0}'}\" />\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"32\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThe **only change** from your current page is adding:\n- `xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"` — import the namespace\n- `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` — declare the binding target type\n\nAll existing `{Binding …}` expressions stay the same — the compiler now resolves them against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nWith `x:DataType` in place, the XAML compiler **already** emits errors for invalid property names. To make sure this is active:\n\n**a) Confirm XamlC is enabled** (it's on by default in MAUI, but to be explicit):\n\n```csharp\n// AssemblyInfo.cs or anywhere at assembly level\n[assembly: XamlCompilation(XamlCompilationOptions.Compile)]\n```\n\n**b) Build and look for errors** — a typo like `{Binding Themee}` now produces:\n\n```\nerror XFC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\"\n```\n\n**c) Opt out locally** when needed (e.g., binding inside a `DataTemplate` to a different type):\n\n```xml\n<DataTemplate x:DataType=\"models:SomeOtherModel\">\n    <Label Text=\"{Binding Name}\" />\n</DataTemplate>\n```\n\nor disable for one binding with `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"`.\n\n### Key points\n\n| Aspect | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **What changes** | Only the `x:DataType` + xmlns on the root element |\n| **Build-time safety** | Misspelled properties, wrong types → compiler errors |\n| **Performance** | Compiled bindings skip runtime reflection — faster |\n| **Escape hatch** | `x:DataType=\"{x:Null}\"` reverts a subtree to reflection |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5c247a21-bcdf-428c-85bc-9e1286839efe","outputTokens":771,"requestId":"A426:278C9F:5E85730:66F6CCF:69F0042A"},"id":"d81376d4-7e21-400e-a100-2ba41c2ead17","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:50:03.191Z","parentId":"3f0c0e10-1c00-4a61-aa9e-3f7f6778eeee"}
